  <body>
    <p>This manuscript describes a very handy new tool for the plotting and handling of chromatograms. ChromatoShiny will allow junior researchers a faster way of representing data, helping streamlining record keeping, data interpretation and representation in most biochemistry laboratories. In particular, this app promises a very intuitive route to clear cross-referencing chromatography profiles with data from SDS-PAGE, Western blot and activity assay analyses.</p>
    <p> This is a clearly written, technically sound report on a useful tool, which can be used by most researchers using chromatography in their experiments.</p>
    <p>Are the conclusions about the tool and its performance adequately supported by the findings presented in the article?</p>
    <p>Yes</p>
